4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROHIBITING ELECTIONEERING AT ALL POLLING LOCATIONS
5 FOR ALL ELECTIONS FROM THE TIME ABSENTEE BALLOTS ARE AVAILABLE UNTIL ALL VOTING IS
6 COMPLETED; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION; AMENDING SECTION 13-35-211, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
7 IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 13-35-211, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "13-35-211. Electioneering -- soliciting information from electors -- exception. (1) (a) A From the
13 start of in-person absentee voting as provided in 13-1-404, 13-1-503, 13-13-205, and 20-20-401, and until the
14 last person in line at a polling location on election day has voted or the polls close, whichever is later, a person
15 may not do any electioneering on election day within any polling place or any building in which an election is
16 being held or within 100 feet of any entrance to the building in which the polling place is located that aids or
17 promotes the success or defeat of any candidate or ballot issue to be voted upon on at the election.
18 (b) Nothing in subsection (1)(a) may be construed to prohibit a person from using a location for a
19 fundraising reception in a building in which an election is being held during the timeframe prescribed in
20 subsection (1)(a) as long as those attending the fundraising reception do not interact with electors who are
21 present in the building to register to vote, obtain a ballot, or cast a ballot.
22 (2) On election day, During the timeframe prescribed in subsection (1)(a), a candidate, a family
23 member of a candidate, or a worker or volunteer for the candidate's campaign may not distribute alcohol,
24 tobacco, food, drink, or anything of value to a voter within a polling place or a building in which an election is
25 being held or within 100 feet of an entrance to the building in which the polling place is located.
26 (3) A person may not buy, sell, give, wear, or display at or about the polls on an election day
27 during the timeframe prescribed in subsection (1)(a) any badge, button, or other insignia that is designed or
28 tends to aid or promote the success or defeat of any candidate or ballot issue to be voted upon on at the
